---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  date: 'January 20, 2025',
  tool1: {
    name: 'Framer AI',
    slug: '/reviews/framer'
  },
  tool2: {
    name: 'Squarespace',
    slug: '/comparisons/webflow-vs-squarespace'
  }
};

const quickVerdict = {
    framer: 'Best for modern design and marketing pages',
    squarespace: 'Best for easy templates and all-in-one',
    winner: 'Framer for design quality, Squarespace for simplicity'
};

---

<Layout title="Framer AI vs Squarespace: Modern AI vs Traditional Templates">

  <StructuredData
    type="WebPage"
    data={{
      name: 'Framer AI vs Squarespace: Modern AI vs Traditional Templates',
      description: 'Framer generates modern designs with AI. Squarespace offers polished templates the traditional way. One\'s the new wave, one\'s the established standard. Here\'s how they compare.',
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/comparisons/framer-vs-squarespace'
    }}
  />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#FFF8F0]">
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[45%] h-full opacity-[0.04]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px);"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-32 h-32 bg-[#F5521A]/5 rounded-tr-[100px]"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">

          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(245,82,26,0.3)]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.15s"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.3s"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              {comparisonData.date} · COMPARISON
            </span>
          </div>

          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-gray-900">
            <span class="block">Framer AI vs Squarespace:</span>
            <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">Modern vs Traditional</span>
          </h1>

          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-800/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              Framer uses AI to generate modern, animated designs in minutes. Squarespace offers professional templates the traditional way—pick a theme, customize settings. One's the new AI wave, one's the established template leader.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <article class="px-6 py-16 lg:py-24">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <div class="bg-[#F5521A]/5 border-l-4 border-[#F5521A] p-6 my-8">
          <p class="text-gray-900">
            <strong>The one-sentence answer:</strong><br />
            Use Framer if you want modern design with animations and AI generation.<br />
            Use Squarespace if you want polished templates with zero learning curve.<br /><br />
            Framer wins on design and speed. Squarespace wins on simplicity and support.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>The fundamental difference
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Framer uses AI to generate custom designs. You describe what you want, Framer builds it with modern aesthetics, animations, and interactions. It's fast but requires some design eye.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Squarespace offers pre-designed templates. You pick a theme, replace content, adjust settings. No AI generation, but the templates are professionally designed and battle-tested. It's the traditional approach—reliable but less custom.
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 p-6 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm">
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Framer AI:</div>
              <p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.framer}</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Squarespace:</div>
              <p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.squarespace}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-300">
            <strong>Verdict:</strong> {quickVerdict.winner}
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Quick comparison
        </h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8">
          <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Metric</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">Framer AI</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">Squarespace</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Winner</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Design quality</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Modern, custom (9.2/10)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Professional templates</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Framer</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Generation speed</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">2-5 minutes (AI)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">30-60 min (manual)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Framer</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">PageSpeed</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">95+</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">70-85</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Framer</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Ease of use</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Medium</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Very Easy</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Squarespace</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Animations</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Built-in, advanced</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Limited</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Framer</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Monthly cost</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">$15-25</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">$16-65</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Framer</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where Framer wins
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">AI generation</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Describe your site, Framer generates it. Custom design, AI-written copy, appropriate images. Squarespace requires manual customization—you pick templates and replace content yourself. Framer is faster if you want AI help.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Animations and interactions</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Scroll animations, hover effects, smooth transitions—Framer excels. Create premium-feeling sites that respond to user interaction. Squarespace has some animations but they're template-dependent and limited.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">PageSpeed</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Framer sites score 95+ on PageSpeed. Squarespace typically scores 70-85. If performance matters for SEO or user experience, Framer wins without optimization effort.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where Squarespace wins
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Zero learning curve</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Squarespace is designed for beginners. Pick a template, click to edit, publish. Framer requires understanding design basics. If you're non-technical and want something that just works, Squarespace is easier.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Customer support</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          24/7 support, phone, chat, extensive help center. Squarespace has been doing this for 20 years. Framer is newer with less mature support. If you need hand-holding, Squarespace wins.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Template variety</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Hundreds of professional templates for every niche—restaurants, portfolios, e-commerce, blogs. All tested and polished. Framer generates custom designs but you're starting from scratch each time.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>So which should you use?
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choose Framer if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <li>You want modern design with animations</li>
          <li>You like the idea of AI generation</li>
          <li>PageSpeed matters to you</li>
          <li>You're okay with a medium learning curve</li>
          <li>You want more design control</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choose Squarespace if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <li>You want something that just works</li>
          <li>You need 24/7 customer support</li>
          <li>You're non-technical</li>
          <li>You like professional templates</li>
          <li>You don't care about custom animations</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Bottom line
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Framer is the new AI wave—modern, fast, beautiful designs, but requires some design sense. Squarespace is the established template leader—reliable, easy, supported, but less custom.<br /><br />
          For designers, marketers, portfolios—Framer's modern aesthetics shine. For local businesses, restaurants, beginners—Squarespace's simplicity wins.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 my-12">
          <a href={comparisonData.tool1.slug} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
            Read Framer review
          </a>
          <a href="/comparisons/webflow-vs-squarespace" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
            Compare Webflow vs Squarespace
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

</Layout>
